  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Resilience in Northern Costa Rica</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The American Red Cross is working with Costa Rican Red Cross, Costa Rican Red Cross branches, communities and schools within the target area of San Carlos in Northern Costa Rica to increase community organization, preparedness and ability to respond to future disasters and local vulnerabilities. The project will focus on the areas of risk management, with activities such as First Aid trainings, creation and training of Community Committees and School brigades and the implementation of the Integrated Participatory Assessment and subsequent development of Community Actions Plans, as well as the area of water and sanitation, with activities such as water supply related micro-projects. This project is funded by the U.S. Agency for International Development&#x2019;s Office of U.S. Foreign Disaster Assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
